pages.transcription:
Utica ??
Dear Sister & [J.E.???}
I wonder whether I had not better send that thin black coat to Theo. Morgan's to be mended. He could probably do it Monday The overcoat might be sent or left till an other time. It also seems that he ought to have pants - I have just called upon Avery. He invited J.E. to go home with him Tues. evening & stay overnight and then he could look around in the a.m. There is a good boarding place next door where he might start perhaps- now to J.G.E. it is much warmer this a.m. Hope to have a letter Mon. morning
